Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. cases #14CF55 and #14CF273 called at 8:38am.
Defendant Tristen C. Seefeld in court with Attorney Yelena O. Zarwell.  ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.  

On Motion of the State, the Court amends Count #1 of Case #14CF273 to Class A Misdemeanor Bailjumping contrary to Statute 946.49(1)(a).

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights given; plea of " No Contest " entered on Case #14CF55 Counts #1 & #2, and on Case #14CF273 on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified as to Case #14CF55; the Court accepts the pleas, finds Mr. Seefeld guilty of all three counts, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.


On Case #14CF55 Count #1 the Court withholds sentence and places Mr. Seefeld on Probation for 30 months.
On Case#14CF55, Count #2 and on Case #14CF273 each, the Court withholds sentence, and places Mr. Seefeld on Probation for 24 months, concurrent.
Conditions of Probation are: 

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with treatment recommendations
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety:  no possession or consumption of alcohol; no possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores
--in Case #14CF55 only: to pay restitution of $611.90 to Kenneth Stevens for the towing bill; the Court allows a thirty day hold-open for the State to submit the victim request and information on restitution for vehicle repair costs
--in Case #14CF55 only: to pay the 10% restitution processing fee
 --to obtain/maintain fulltime employment and/or education program as required by the Agent
--in Case #14CF55, Count #1 only: to comply with DNA sample provision
--in Case #14CF55, Count #1: to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge

--in Case #14CF55, Count #2: to pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge
--in Case #14CF273: to pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge


Days credit for time already served in Case #14CF55: 0  days
Days credit for time already served in Case #14CF273: 2  days

As to Case #14CF55 only, the Court indicates that if Mr. Seefeld successfully completes the Probation terms, the case will be expunged.
